thread.title: Impressive debut for Chandrasekar
thread.title_full: Impressive debut for Chandrasekar - The Times of India

author: Prasad RS
title: Impressive debut for Chandrasekar
text:
CHENNAI: Tamil Nadu's left-arm spinner DT Chandrasekar shone in his debut Ranji Trophy game against Baroda when he took 4 for 50 at the MA Chidambaram Stadium here on Friday morning. What was impressive about Chandrasekar was his ability to fox the batsmen on a regular basis with his probing line and length.
With just 125 on board in the first innings, Chandrasekar was brought into the attack by skipper Abhinav Mukund early on the second day of the contest. In his very first over, Chandrasekar got rid of Baroda skipper Aditya Waghmode who was looking dangerous. From that point of time, the match turned on its head and Tamil Nadu went on to restrict their opponents to 159 in the first innings.
Chandrasekar is someone who has been a consistent performer and has over 100 wickets to his credit in the first division league over the past two years.
